parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module/HCU can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to unpredictable braking and loss of traction control, which can result in accidents, especially in slippery conditions.
symptoms: Intermittent or constant warning lights for ABS
and electronic braking system; beeping or chiming noises; loss of cruise control; and unpredictable braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy; the brake pedal sticks to the floor; the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and traction control system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS and traction control lights come on; the vehicle slides or skids while braking; the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power steering fluid leak can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle.
